## Description {#details}

This file defines the GCNRegPressure class, which tracks registry pressure by bookkeeping number of SGPR/VGPRs used, weights for large SGPR/VGPRs.

It also implements a compare function, which compares different register pressures, and declares one with max occupancy as winner.

<Link id="l00084" /><CodeLine lineNumber="84"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Compares \\p this GCNRegpressure to \\p O, returning true if \\p this is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00085" /><CodeLine lineNumber="85"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// less. Since GCNRegpressure contains different types of pressures, and due</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00086" /><CodeLine lineNumber="86"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// to target-specific pecularities (e.g. we care about occupancy rather than</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00087" /><CodeLine lineNumber="87"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// raw register usage), we determine if \\p this GCNRegPressure is less than</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00088" /><CodeLine lineNumber="88"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// \\p O based on the following tiered comparisons (in order order of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00089" /><CodeLine lineNumber="89"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// precedence):</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00090" /><CodeLine lineNumber="90"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// 1 Better occupancy</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00091" /><CodeLine lineNumber="91"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// 2 Less spilling (first preference to VGPR spills, then to SGPR spills)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00092" /><CodeLine lineNumber="92"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// 3 Less tuple register pressure (first preference to VGPR tuples if we</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00093" /><CodeLine lineNumber="93"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// determine that SGPR pressure is not important)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="94"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// 4 Less raw register pressure (first preference to VGPR tuples if we</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="95"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// determine that SGPR pressure is not important)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="96"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gcnregpressure/#aec7a7a1abbcf26f495eb5057cb42f311">less</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinefunction">MachineFunction</a> &amp;MF, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gcnregpressure">GCNRegPressure</a> &amp;O,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00097" /><CodeLine lineNumber="97"><Highlight kind="normal">            </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> MaxOccupancy = std::numeric&#95;limits&lt;unsigned&gt;::max()) </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
